3. Relationships
Parent Table	Child Table	Relationship
PropertyOwner	Property	One Owner → Many Properties (1:M)
Agent	Property	One Agent → Many Properties (1:M)
PropertyType	Property	One Type → Many Properties (1:M)
Property	Visit	One Property → Many Visits (1:M)
Customer	Visit	One Customer → Many Visits (1:M)
Property	Sale	One Property → One Sale (1:1 after sale)
Customer	Sale	One Customer → Many Purchases (1:M)
Property	Rental	One Property → Many Rentals over time (1:M)
Customer	Rental	One Customer → Many Rentals (1:M)
Customer	Payment	One Customer → Many Payments (1:M)
Property	Payment	One Property → Many Payments (1:M)

5. Normalization
First Normal Form (1NF)
Each table has a primary key.
No repeating groups.
Each field contains only one value.

Result: ✔ Achieved

Second Normal Form (2NF)
All non-key attributes depend on the entire primary key.
No partial dependency.

Result: ✔ Achieved

Third Normal Form (3NF)
No transitive dependencies.
Attributes depend only on the primary key.

Result: ✔ Achieved

